<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-11-22T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-11-22T07:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.7412A/13: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kodding</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-22T14:00:00+02:00">November 22, 1928—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:42 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>30. Mr. Minkoff<note n="5" xml:id="d15fn5">Secretary General of the
                                Bulgarian Foreign Office.</note> informs me that Bulgarian Legation
                            in Washington was instructed yesterday by telegraph to sign the proposed
                            treaties of arbitration and conciliation without modifications.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kodding</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>